{"id":22,"parent_id":6,"book_id":9402,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":22,"title":"Moses 6:1–25: The Generations of Adam","subtitle":"","short_title":"Moses 6:1–25: The Generations of Adam","uri":"/manual/the-pearl-of-great-price-teacher-manual/the-book-of-moses/moses-61-25-the-generations-of-adam","content":[["div",{"id":"head17","uri":"/manual/the-pearl-of-great-price-teacher-manual/the-book-of-moses/moses-61-25-the-generations-of-adam.head17"},["h1","Moses 6:1–25",["br"],"The Generations of Adam"]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Some Important Principles, Doctrines, and Events"],["ul.bullet",["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","The priesthood was passed in a patriarchal order from Adam to his son Seth (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.2-3,7"},"Moses 6:2–3, 7"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/107.40-42"},"D&C 107:40–42"],")."]],["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","Since the time of Adam and Eve, people have written, learned from, and taught from inspired writings (the scriptures). These writings have included family lineage and the inspired actions and sayings of family members (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.5-23,46"},"Moses 6:5–23, 46"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/24.32"},"Luke 24:32"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/4.1-6"},"Jacob 4:1–6"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/18.38-39"},"Alma 18:38–39"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/20.8-13,17-26,35"},"D&C 20:8–13, 17–26, 35"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/abr/1.28,31"},"Abraham 1:28, 31"],")."]],["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","Those who accept the gospel are often called the “sons of God” or the “children of God.” Those who have not yet accepted the gospel or have rejected it are called the “sons of men,” “daughters of men,” or “children of men” (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/5.52-56"},"Moses 5:52–56"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.8,15,23,68"},"6:8, 15, 23, 68"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/2.27"},"2 Nephi 2:27"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/14.28-31"},"Helaman 14:28–31"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.1"},"Moses 7:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/8.13-15,19-21"},"8:13–15, 19–21"],")."]]]],[".topic",["h2","Suggestions for Teaching"],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6"},"Moses 6"],". Overview"],["div",{"id":"p162","uri":"/manual/the-pearl-of-great-price-teacher-manual/the-book-of-moses/moses-61-25-the-generations-of-adam.p162"},"Assign pairs of students to make charts showing the names and ages of the patriarchs mentioned in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.10-25"},"Moses 6:10–25"],"(see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/8.1-12"},"Moses 8:1–12"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/7.1-6"},"Genesis 7:1–6"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/9.28-29"},"9:28–29"],"). Ask students what they learn from this chart about the early patriarchs. What book did Enoch preach from? (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.46"},"Moses 6:46"],"). Why did Enoch preach? (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.27-30,42,68"},"vv. 27–30, 42, 68"],")."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.1-3,10-16"},"Moses 6:1–3, 10–16"],". Seth Was a Worthy Son"],["div",{"id":"p163","uri":"/manual/the-pearl-of-great-price-teacher-manual/the-book-of-moses/moses-61-25-the-generations-of-adam.p163"},"Have students study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/5.16-21"},"Moses 5:16–21"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.1-3,10-16"},"6:1–3, 10–16"],"and compare Cain, Abel, and Seth (see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/107.42-43,53"},"D&C 107:42–43, 53"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/138.40"},"138:40"],")."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.5"},"Moses 6:5"],". A Book of Remembrance"],["div",{"id":"p164","uri":"/manual/the-pearl-of-great-price-teacher-manual/the-book-of-moses/moses-61-25-the-generations-of-adam.p164"},"Have students read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/68.2-4"},"Doctrine and Covenants 68:2–4"],"and tell what these verses teach about scripture. Read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.5"},"Moses 6:5"],"and ask students how they think",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/68.2-4"},"Doctrine and Covenants 68:2–4"],"applies to the book of remembrance kept by Adam. Read and discuss the statement by Elder Bruce R. McConkie of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles in the commentary for",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.5-6"},"Moses 6:5–6"],"in the student manual (p. 19)."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.15"},"Moses 6:15"],". The Children of Men"],["div",{"id":"p165","uri":"/manual/the-pearl-of-great-price-teacher-manual/the-book-of-moses/moses-61-25-the-generations-of-adam.p165"},"Show students that in the book of Moses two groups or types of people are mentioned: the “children of God” or “sons of God,” who were righteous (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.8,68"},"Moses 6:8, 68"],"), and the “children of men” or “sons of men,” who had not yet accepted or who had rejected the gospel (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/5.52"},"Moses 5:52"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.15,23"},"6:15, 23"],"). Assign a few students to tell what they learn in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/5.52-56"},"Moses 5:52–56"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.15"},"6:15"],"about the children of men, and assign others to tell what they learn about the children of God in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.8-14,16-25"},"Moses 6:8–14, 16–25"],"."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.15"},"Moses 6:15"],". Satan “Raged in Their Hearts”"],["div",{"id":"p166","uri":"/manual/the-pearl-of-great-price-teacher-manual/the-book-of-moses/moses-61-25-the-generations-of-adam.p166"},"Read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.15"},"Moses 6:15"],"and ask students what the words",["span.emphasis","dominion"],"and",["span.emphasis","rage"],"mean. What did Satan’s dominion and rage lead to in the days of Seth? Discuss what",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/28.20-22"},"2 Nephi 28:20–22"],"teaches about Satan’s methods in the last days. How is Satan able to get into people’s hearts?"]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.23"},"Moses 6:23"],". Preachers of Righteousness"],["div",{"id":"p167","uri":"/manual/the-pearl-of-great-price-teacher-manual/the-book-of-moses/moses-61-25-the-generations-of-adam.p167"},"Have students tell what they learn about the preaching of righteousness in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.23"},"Moses 6:23"],"and",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/4.19"},"Alma 4:19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/17.9-17"},"17:9–17"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/31.5"},"31:5"],". Point out that in the remaining verses of",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6"},"Moses 6–7"],"there are several excellent examples of true preachers of righteousness. Ask students to name people in the Church today who could be called “preachers of righteousness.”"]]]]],"refs":null}
